Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addModuleToFPlan(25.10)                                addModuleToFPlan(25.10)

Name
       addModuleToFPlan - Use this command to display modules in the floorplan
       view  whose  instance count is smaller than the setPreference MinFPMod-
       uleSize value

Syntax
        addModuleToFPlan

       [-help]

       hInstName

       [add_or_remove]

       Use this command to display modules in the  floorplan  view  whose  in-
       stance  count  is smaller than the setPreference MinFPModuleSize value.
       By default, modules whose instance count is less  than  MinFPModuleSize
       are  not  displayed (default is 1). The MinFPModuleSize variable can be
       set to a larger value to focus only on  larger  modules  which  require
       floorplanning. You can then display specific smaller modules using this
       command. For example, use addModuleToFPlan if you need to interactively
       floorplan small regions or fences to control placement of small modules
       of logic.

       Note: You can change the Min. floorplan Module Size option in the Pref-
       erences  form in the Display menu and import the design. Alternatively,
       you can use the setPreference MinFPModuleSize <value> command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each addModuleToFPlan parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

              man addModuleToFPlan

       <hInstName>
              Specifies the name of the hierarchical instance.

              Data_type: string, required

       <add_or_remove>
              Adds  or  removes the specified hierarchical instance. Specify 1
              to add or 0 to remove.

              Data_type: int, optional

Example
              * The following command adds hierarchical instance SH99  in  the
                floorplan view:

                addModuleToFPlan SH99 1

              * The following command only displays modules with 200 instances
                or more:

                setPreference MinFPModuleSize 200

                If  module  mcore0/a0 has less than 200 instances you can dis-
                play it using:

                addModuleToFPlan mcore0/a0 1

                To disable its display:

                addModuleToFPlan mcore0/a0 0

Related Information
              * setPreference

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

